        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "feat(telegram): opt-in interleaved progress lane",
        "body": "Add an opt-in Telegram progress projection that renders already-authorized structured runtime events into one durable live message, matching CLI ergonomics without changing execution semantics or exposing new data by default.\n\n## What this does\n\nWhen `channels.telegram.streaming.preview.interleavedProgress` is enabled, reasoning text and the existing structured runtime events are rendered into a **single durable live message** on the reasoning lane (Codex/Claude-CLI style), instead of the separate tool-progress lane.\n\nIt consumes the **existing** agent-event callbacks with **no contract change** — `onReasoningStream`, `onToolStart`, `onItemEvent`, `onPlanUpdate`, `onApprovalEvent`, `onCommandOutput`, `onPatchSummary` — and falls back to the current `pushStreamToolProgress` lane whenever the flag is off.\n\n## Scope boundary\n\nProjection-only. It does **not** change prompts, model routing, tool execution, auth, or default visibility — it only changes Telegram rendering, and only when explicitly enabled.\n\n- **Default off.** Gated on preview tool progress already being enabled **and** an explicit opt-in **and** a reasoning lane existing, so it inherits every existing group/DM/visibility gate and cannot expose anything the tool-progress lane wasn't already authorized to show.\n- **No raw data.** Tool lines show the tool name only (never raw args); item/plan/approval/command/patch lines show the title only (never raw command output); every line is whitespace-collapsed and length-capped.\n- **No new event contract** (Pass 1). The shared structured-event contract already exists in `src/infra/agent-events.ts`; this PR only adds a Telegram renderer over it. Extracting/normalizing a shared contract is deliberately deferred to a follow-up once the UX is proven.\n\n## Changes\n\n- `src/config/types.telegram.ts` + `src/config/zod-schema.providers-core.ts`: add the opt-in `streaming.preview.interleavedProgress` flag.\n- `extensions/telegram/src/interleaved-progress.ts`: pure render helpers (gate, sanitize/cap, header-strip, message render, reasoning checkpoint, status-line append).\n- `extensions/telegram/src/bot-message-dispatch.ts`: wire the 7 callbacks through the renderer with fallback; clear the rolling timer in the run's `finally`.\n\n## Tests\n\n`extensions/telegram/src/interleaved-progress.test.ts` (18 cases) covers:\n- disabled-by-default, explicit opt-out, tool-progress-off, and no-reasoning-lane (room-event / source-delivery-suppressed) all leave the gate off → current behaviour preserved, no progress leak.\n- single `Thinking` header (no duplication); body stored header-stripped.\n- rolling-timer suffix present while running, dropped (shorter strict-prefix) once cleared so a full-text lane update replaces stale timer text instead of appending.\n- whitespace-collapse + length cap so no large/secret-looking value floods a line.\n- reasoning checkpoint appends only newly-arrived text on cumulative re-delivery.\n\n## Not yet covered\n\n- End-to-end integration through the dispatch harness (timer-interval clearing on every exit path is wired in the run's `finally`; 429/backoff uses `stream.update` not forced flush — both verified by construction/reading, not yet by a harness test).\n- Live current-head Telegram capture.",
